{"parentUuid":"49fcce5d-3e96-4e95-b8d3-df1955835cc5","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"c6161356-8db5-4013-885d-7e73eaa173ba","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the items don't have a 'rarity' field in the current data model. The taxonomy is by 'type': monster_core, herb, equipment, consumable, heavenly_flame, book, quest, currency, material.\n\nThe user's point is: high-value items should NOT be:\n1. Sold in commercial streets (商店没有)\n2. Found through casual gathering (采集不到)\n\nThey should be:\n1. Dropped by bosses (boss掉落)\n2. Sold by special NPCs with conditions (特殊NPC条件购买)\n3. Rewarded from specific encounters (奇遇奖励)\n\nLet me now take the practical approach:\n1. Remove the gathering spots for high-value items (龙鳞碎片, 菩提叶, 妖火结晶, 龙涎灵草, 远古遗物, 禁药配方残页, 化形草, etc.)\n2. Add drop tables to appropriate bosses\n3. Keep common items in shops/gathering\n4. Add encounter-based acquisition for rare items\n\nThe key distinction:\n- **Commercial streets** → buy common consumables, basic herbs, basic materials with silver\n- **Gathering** → common/uncommon herbs, basic monster cores, regional common specialties\n- **Encounters** → rare items as rewards for specific choices\n- **Boss drops** → legendary items\n- **Special NPCs** → rare/legendary with conditions\n\nLet me create a fix script.","signature":"c6161356-8db5-4013-885d-7e73eaa173ba"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2321,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":261120,"output_tokens":2029,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"a6598229-031f-4da2-8524-f453dc0426b6","timestamp":"2026-06-09T02:32:46.223Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"D:\\work