{"parentUuid":"56b910dc-cbab-42b7-a348-7a62b807b9d7","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"f116863c-ee8e-427d-9869-edc8eb6d2121","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the current system. Skills are defined separately and have effects like `atk:+30`, `hp:+100`, etc. Enemies don't currently have a `skills` field - the combat system uses the enemy's base stats (atk, def, spd, hp).\n\nTo add enemy skills, I need to:\n1. Add a `skills` field to the enemy data structure\n2. Add many more skills to the skill library\n3. Assign skills to each enemy tier\n4. Assign unique skills to bosses\n\nLet me first understand how combat uses skills. Looking at engine.py, the combat system has `combat_skills()` which returns player-known skills. For enemies, the combat seems to use basic attack/defend.\n\nThe simplest approach that adds value:\n1. Add a `Skills` column to the Enemies sheet\n2. Add it to the parser in workbook.py\n3. Design a skill tier system\n4. Assign skills to all enemies\n\nBut this could get very complex. Let me focus on what the user asked:\n1. Design skills for each enemy tier (mob/elite/boss)\n2. Generic skills for mobs based on element/type\n3. Elite skills\n4. Boss unique skills from the novel\n\nLet me plan the skill tiers:\n\n**Tier 1 - Common (Lv 1-20)**: Basic attacks, simple elements\n- 普通攻击, 冲撞, 撕咬, 爪击, 尾击\n- 火球, 冰锥, 风刃, 地刺, 水箭\n\n**Tier 2 - Advanced Common (Lv 20-40)**: Elemental enhancements\n- 烈焰冲击, 冰霜新星, 旋风斩, 地震术, 水龙卷\n- 毒雾, 麻痹毒液, 催眠粉\n\n**Tier 3 - Elite (Lv 30-55)**: Special techniques\n- 血爆术, 灵魂冲击, 暗影步, 剑气斩\n- 火焰风暴, 冰封万里, 雷霆一击\n\n**Tier 4 - Advanced Elite (Lv 50-75)**: Powerful abilities\n- 空间撕裂, 灵魂锁链, 天雷降世, 地火焚天\n- 龙威, 远古咆哮, 虚空吞噬\n\n**Tier 5 - Boss Unique**: Novel-specific skills\n- 美杜莎: 石化魔眼\n- 韩枫: 海心焰·焚海\n- 云山: 风之极·陨杀\n- 魂天帝: 魂帝·万魂噬天\n- etc.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The current game has 59 skills. I should expand the skill library and then assign skills to enemies. But coupling enemy skills to the player skill system adds complexity.\n\nA simpler approach: Add a `Skills` field to each enemy that contains a comma-separated list of skill IDs or inline skill definitions. The combat system can then reference these.\n\nBut modifying the combat system is a deep change. Let me take the user's request at face value: they want me to DESIGN what skills each enemy tier should have, and what boss-unique skills exist. I can encode this in the enemy data and create the skill definitions.\n\nLet me create:\n1. ~100 new skill definitions\n2. Skill assignment rules by enemy type/level\n3. Boss unique skills\n\nThen append the skill assignments to the enemy records.\n\nActually, given the complexity, let me organize this as:\n1. New skills added to Skills sheet\n2. A new field or mapping for enemy skills\n3. Document the design clearly\n\nLet me create the comprehensive script.","signature":"f116863c-ee8e-427d-9869-edc8eb6d2121"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1857,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":307584,"output_tokens":908,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"c7a12a3a-21d5-4091-a9d3-da22db865434","timestamp":"2026-06-09T03:09:53.165Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"D:\\work\\wordworld","sessionId":"00d28fbf-7def-43f1-8f03-9196876513ea","version":"2.1.169","gitBranch":"master","slug":"eager-weaving-neumann"}
