{"parentUuid":"ab42b520-1c86-449b-b87b-f181563b9bfe","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"495d615f-9d2b-4509-b273-6bc594db7fa5","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The search reveals which abilities are actually in the novel text and which I made up. Let me now do a deeper search focusing on:\n\n1. What the novel actually says about each character's combat abilities\n2. Common monster behaviors described in the novel\n3. What generic skills make sense based on the novel's power system\n\nKey findings from the search:\n- Many skills I created (like 撕咬, 爪击, 火球, 冰锥) are generic monster behaviors that exist in any fantasy novel but aren't specifically named in the text\n- Some boss skills I assigned don't match the novel (e.g., 云山 uses \"风壁\" not \"风之极陨杀\" as a named skill)\n- The novel uses specific斗技 names for human characters and generic descriptions for monsters\n\nLet me now create a properly documented skill design that:\n1. References the novel for every named character's abilities\n2. Uses reasonable inference for monsters based on the novel's power system\n3. Clearly marks what's from the novel vs. what's inferred\n\nLet me write a comprehensive design document, then redo the skill assignments properly.","signature":"495d615f-9d2b-4509-b273-6bc594db7fa5"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1681,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":324352,"output_tokens":7315,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"460e5b9b-9c0e-40e3-b4d3-49dfe0fce648","timestamp":"2026-06-09T03:15:13.764Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"D:\\work\\wordworld","sessionId":"00d28fbf-7def-43f1-8f03-9196876513ea","version":"2.1.16